        "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
        "score": 3,
        "is_accepted": false,
        "last_activity_date": 1400440730,
        "creation_date": 1400440730,
        "body": "<pre><code>        Class.forName(\"oracle.jdbc.driver.OracleDriver\");\n        Connection connection = \n            DriverManager.getConnection\n            (\"jdbc:oracle:thin:@localhost:1521:MySID\",\"username\",\"password\");\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>If you use <code>:<\/code> (<code>jdbc:oracle:thin:@localhost:1521:MySID<\/code>) - after that, the SID name is expected. \nIf you use <code>/<\/code> (<code>jdbc:oracle:thin:@localhost:1521/MySERVICE<\/code>) - the service name is expected<\/p>\n\n<p>More here: <a href=\"http://www.orafaq.com/wiki/JDBC\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.orafaq.com/wiki/JDBC<\/a><\/p>\n",
        "answer_id": 23725888,
